                        <p class="card-text">Sacramento Kings center Hassan Whiteside will miss
                            his
                            third
                            straight contest on Monday against San Antonio. Whiteside has been
                            dealing
                            with
                            a
                            sore knee, though it's at least a good sign that he was initially
                            listed
                            as
                            questionable. His absence will mean that Richaun Holmes will
                            continue to
                            dominate
                            the frontcourt touches for Sacramento, though forwards Chimezie Metu
                            and
                            Chris
                            Silva
                            could have solid games if they see added minutes. Metu has been
                            earning
                            more
                            trust
                            with the coaching staff lately, as he has 13 points, nine rebounds,
                            and
                            three
                            blocks
                            in his last 30 minutes across two contests.</p>
                    </blockquote>

