                    <blockquote class="blockquote">
                        <p class="card-text">Toronto Raptors guard Kyle Lowry (foot) will be
                            sidelined
                            for
                            7-10 days, per Blake Murphy of The Athletic. Lowry was ruled out
                            early
                            for
                            Wednesday's game, with head coach Nick Nurse saying that the veteran
                            guard's
                            toe
                            infection \"is not going well.\" With Lowry out for a week, guards
                            Fred
                            VanVleet
                            and Gary Trent Jr. will shoulder a bigger scoring load in the
                            backcourt.
                            Guard
                            Rodney Hood and forward Stanley Johnson could also see expanded
                            roles
                            for
                            Toronto. VanVleet and Trent should be the more reliable DFS plays of
                            the
                            bunch.
                        </p>
                    </blockquote>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary news-btn">View Full Story</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

