                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title newsTitle">Luka Doncic, Kristaps Porzingis Ruled Out
                        Saturday
                    </h5>
                    <blockquote class="blockquote">
                        <p class="card-text">"Dallas Mavericks guard Luka Doncic (illness) and
                            center
                            Kristaps Porzingis (knee) have been ruled out for Saturday's contest
                            against
                            the
                            Pelicans. Doncic's status was already up-in-the-air due to back
                            tightness,
                            but
                            he contracted a non-COVD related illness, all but ensuring he
                            wouldn't
                            suit
                            up.
                            Porzingis will sit for the second half of the team's back-to-back.
                            Jalen
                            Brunson, Josh Richardson, and Tim Hardaway Jr. should all get a ton
                            of
                            scoring
                            and playmaking opportunities on Saturday without Doncic and
                            Porzingis.
                            Dwight
                            Powell and Maxi Kleber should see most of Porzingis' minutes- though
                            Boban
                            Marjanovic could also make an appearance on the court.
                        </p>
                    </blockquote>

                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary news-btn">View Full Story</a>
